contentrichtext.text: '''Joseph''' or '''Joe Taylor''' may refer to: ==Missionaries== * [[Joseph Taylor (missionary)]] (died 1859), London Missionary Society missionary in Gujarat, India * [[J. V. S. Taylor]] (died 1881), his son, British missionary in India ==Politicians== * [[Joseph D. Taylor]] (1830–1899), U.S. Representative from Ohio * [[Joseph Edward Taylor]] (1830–1913), Utah politician and undertaker ==Sportsmen== * [[Joe Taylor (American football)]] (born 1939), former professional American football cornerback * [[Joe Taylor (baseball)]] (1926–1993), American professional baseball outfielder * [[Joseph Taylor (footballer)]] (1851–1888), 1870s Scottish footballer ==Academics== * [[Joseph T. Taylor]] (1913–2000), dean of Indiana University * [[Joe Gray Taylor]] (1920–1987), historian * [[Joseph Hooton Taylor, Jr.]] (born 1941), American astrophysicist ==Others== * [[Joseph W. Taylor]] (1810-1880), physician and Quaker * [[Joseph Pannell Taylor]] (1796–1864), brother of Zachary Taylor, American Civil War general * [[Joseph Taylor (17th-century actor)]] (died 1652), Richard Burbage's successor with the King's Men * [[Joey Taylor]] of the band ''Undercover'' {{hndis|Taylor, Joseph}}
